						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Two sides of the elephant-stone (āne-kallu) set up in front of the wall of the Hanumān Temple.</hi></p>						

						<p>Amōghavarsha—A.D. 941-42.</p>						

						<p>The record is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 863</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 941-42.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription is very severely damaged. The letters <hi rend="italic">Amō</hi> in line 11 suggest that the inscription belongs to <hi rend="bold">Amōghavarsha.</hi> </p>						

